replies.text:
@Reuben Longworth:  Respectfully:
1. With the exception of his not placing a lid on his liquid resistor setup, what Robs demonstrated in this video (Particularly the the bit with him holding the conductors) is no more dangerous than simple arc welding. In fact, the fact that he double insulated his leads AND put on rubber gloves in addition to welding gauntlets makes his precautions in that portion of the video far exceed the safety steps practiced by professional welders, who quite often will arc weld with a bare clamp on their welding table (making the WHOLE TABLE PART OF THE CIRCUIT)  and their rod clamp lead (single insulated) in hand with only (sometimes) leather gloves on (no rubber or plastic liners), while leaning against (or on) the metal table. Please refer to the hundreds of welding instructional videos on YT and elsewhere produced and posted by leading manufactures of welding equipment & professional welders for confirmation of this.
2.  Again, respectfully.  Can you please post a link or some form of evidence that Rob or anyone for that matter (aside from their direct legal guardians and specific governmental office holders tasked expressly with doing so) has ANY   obligation or responsibility for the well being of anyone, save those they have voluntarily chosen to look after?
